A PV system with 4 PV modules configured in series is connected to the standalone loads using a boost converter shown in Fig. 2a which is considered for simulation studies. The parameters of the boost converter and algorithms data values have to be shown in Table 3. The simulation outcome is executed by applying the proposed Bayesian fusion optimization technique (BFT) to get the global maximum power point (GMPP) in MATLAB/SIMULINK for three possible patterns shown in Table 1 under the PSCs. The performance of the proposed method is evaluated by comparing it with the existing methods such as the incremental conductance method, PSO method, and Jaya method. Three different case studies are performed with three different partially shaded conditions of the PV system as detailed below.
